# LegacyLens

> Help developers understand legacy code through AI + static analysis verification

## Quick Start

### 1. System Requirements

- **OS:** Debian 13+ / Ubuntu 22.04+
- **Python:** 3.10+
- **RAM:** 16GB recommended
- **CPU:** Intel i5 or equivalent

### 2. Setup Environment

```bash
cd /home/knaaps/Desktop/project/LegacyLens

# Create virtual environment
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate

# Install dependencies
pip install -e ".[dev]"
```

### 3. Install Ollama (Local LLM)

```bash
# Install Ollama
curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh

# Start Ollama service
systemctl --user start ollama
# Or run directly: ollama serve

# Download the model (~4GB)
ollama pull deepseek-coder:6.7b
```

### 4. Clone Test Repositories

```bash
# Easy mode - well-structured Spring Boot app
git clone https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-petclinic.git data/spring-petclinic

# Hard mode - complex legacy Java project
git clone https://github.com/apache/ant.git data/apache-ant
```

### 5. Run Tests

```bash
pytest tests/ -v
```

### 6. Usage

```bash
# Index a repository
legacylens index data/spring-petclinic

# Query code
legacylens query "What does the OwnerController do?"
```

## Project Structure

```
src/legacylens/
├── parser/          # Code parsing (tree-sitter)
├── embeddings/      # CodeBERT + ChromaDB
├── retrieval/       # RAG pipeline
├── agents/          # Writer-Critic verification (Phase 2)
└── main.py          # CLI entry point
```

## Architecture

```
User Query → Parser → Embeddings → Retriever → Writer-Critic → Response
                ↓           ↓
           Static Facts  Vector DB
```

